programme.title: 21 Jump Street
programme.desc: Trying to prove themselves, two newly-graduated police officers work undercover as two teenagers in a high school, to uncover drug traffickers who dominate the school.(n)

programme.title: Hitman: Agent 47
programme.desc: An elite assassin, genetically engineered to be the perfect killing machine, known only by the last two digits on the barcode tattooed on the back of his neck; 47, teams up with a young woman, targeting a mega-corporation planning to unlock the secret of Agent 47's past to create an army of killers.(n)

programme.title: Queen of Spades: The Looking Glass
programme.desc: The Queen of Spades is back and is blood-thirsty, and this time she has chosen the students of a boarding school who find a mysterious mirror with strange drawings in an abandoned wing.(n)

programme.title: Divergent
programme.desc: In a future Chicago setting, people are divided into five distinct factions based on their personalities. Beatrice discovers that she is Divergent, meaning she does not fit into any one faction, and soon uncovers a sinister plot brewing in her seemingly perfect society.(n)

programme.title: Painted Skin: The Resurrection
programme.desc: The malevolent fox spirit Xiaowei (Xun Zhou) is looking for a freely given heart to become human, while Princess Jing (Wei Zhao) searches for her true love, wearing a golden mask to hide her facial scars.(n)

programme.title: The Monkey King
programme.desc: A monkey with supernatural powers, must battle forces of demons to find his place back in the heavens.(n)

programme.title: I, Robot
programme.desc: In the distant future, robots are created to help humans with their daily tasks. He must take care of all those troubles before starting a new life.(n)
